02:01.676 --> 02:03.611
10-13! 10-13!

02:03.612 --> 02:05.312
Corner of Beaver and Williams,
in Manhattan.

02:05.313 --> 02:06.313
I repeat, 10-13!

02:06.314 --> 02:07.815
This is Car One.

02:07.816 --> 02:09.984
It's Reagan.
The PC's been shot.

02:13.905 --> 02:15.890
<i>In a word: lucky.</i>

02:15.891 --> 02:18.909
He took some shot
to his left arm and chest

02:18.910 --> 02:21.045
that impacted the artery
but missed the heart.

02:21.046 --> 02:22.529
Is he talking?
Is he sedated?

02:22.530 --> 02:24.197
Oh, yeah, he's talking.
He's already trying

02:24.198 --> 02:25.299
to talk his way out of here.

02:25.300 --> 02:26.500
How long before
he gets to go home?

02:26.501 --> 02:28.535
Uh, we'll hold him
for two days, minimum.

02:28.536 --> 02:30.170
I want to keep him
under observation

02:30.171 --> 02:31.755
to make sure there's no
pulmonary involvement.

02:31.756 --> 02:33.908
But he's going to be okay.

02:33.909 --> 02:36.727
He's in remarkably great shape.
And, as I said, very lucky.

02:36.728 --> 02:37.811
Here we are.

02:37.812 --> 02:39.346
Okay.
Go ahead, Grandpa.

02:40.482 --> 02:42.616
Hi, Dad.

02:42.617 --> 02:45.319
Hey.

02:48.690 --> 02:50.774
I'm going to be fine. Promise.

02:50.775 --> 02:51.759
You're looking at

02:51.760 --> 02:53.794
one grateful
bunch, Francis.

02:53.795 --> 02:56.630
What can you
tell us, Dad?

02:56.631 --> 02:58.933
They ruined my best blazer.

03:00.335 --> 03:01.569
About the shooter.

03:01.570 --> 03:05.606
I know, Danny.

03:08.476 --> 03:10.878
I don't know much.

03:13.582 --> 03:15.816
Dark sedan.

03:15.817 --> 03:18.519
I'm sure my guys
got the make.

03:18.520 --> 03:22.089
Shotgun, obviously.

03:22.958 --> 03:25.225
This one was a flyer.

03:27.762 --> 03:29.964
Most likely a sawed-off shotgun

03:29.965 --> 03:32.266
because, uh...

03:32.267 --> 03:34.168
a blast came
from inside the car.

03:35.971 --> 03:39.206
I didn't see the shooter.

03:39.207 --> 03:42.176
Think for a second, Dad.

03:42.177 --> 03:44.912
I am thinking, son.

03:44.913 --> 03:47.448
Dad, was he
white, black,

03:47.449 --> 03:49.216
clean-shaven, beard?

03:49.217 --> 03:50.751
Can you remember anything?

03:50.752 --> 03:52.786
What happened to Walter?

03:52.787 --> 03:54.555
He's fine.

03:54.556 --> 03:55.856
A sprained wrist
from breaking his fall.

03:55.857 --> 03:57.324
Good.

03:57.325 --> 04:01.962
I just wouldn't forgive myself
if anything happened to Walter.

04:01.963 --> 04:03.597
Maybe, Doctor,

04:03.598 --> 04:05.816
you could, uh...

04:05.817 --> 04:07.735
check on Walter.

04:07.736 --> 04:09.820
Dad, can you just try
to remember anything...

04:09.821 --> 04:11.238
He's still
in some shock.

04:11.239 --> 04:12.339
Commissioner,

04:12.340 --> 04:14.341
I'm going to take your
family downstairs

04:14.342 --> 04:15.776
to get some of our
wretched coffee

04:15.777 --> 04:17.778
and then we'll check back
with you in a little while.

04:19.113 --> 04:21.315
We'll be right outside, okay?

04:29.991 --> 04:31.358
Reagan.

04:32.827 --> 04:34.828
Yeah?

04:34.829 --> 04:36.096
No. No, no, no. You wait.

04:36.097 --> 04:37.665
I'm coming down.

04:37.666 --> 04:40.067
Yeah.

04:50.011 --> 04:52.479
These guys are toast.

